          "pos": "verb",
          "definition": "past tense of tiptoe; walked quietly on the tips of the toes",
          "examples": [
            "She tiptoed into the room and closed the door softly.",
            "He tiptoed past the sleeping dog."
          ],
          "collocations": [
            "tiptoed back",
            "tiptoed away"
